  "articleSummary": "The article argues that local Docker development environments are often overlooked security targets, exposing developers to risks like intercepted traffic and unprotected services. It provides practical fixes, including using private Docker networks instead of relying on firewalls, configuring UFW with Docker (which bypasses default rules), and validating secrets to prevent placeholder leaks. The tone is a tutorial with urgent warnings, targeting developers who casually connect to public Wi-Fi or trust local networks. Recurring framing includes \"we've all done it\" confessions and emphasis on common misconceptions, such as the false security of binding ports to local IP addresses.",
